item.title: Project 2: Euler's projects
item.description: Overview This is the second project for BIOSTAT 823 (2020 Fall) This project requires to solve three problems from Euler’s Project. I choose my two of the problems related to decimals, and one related to prime numbers. The detailed solution and codes are in here. I will explain my solutions to each of the problems in the following sections: Problem 7: 10001st prime (420,695) Problem: By listing the first six prime numbers: 2, 3, 5, 7, 11, and 13, we can see that the 6th prime is 13.
